<HL>
   Business Brief -- Polaroid Corp.:
   Venture Is Set With China
   For Instant-Camera Firm
</HL>
<DATE>
09/07/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   PRD FREST
</CO>
<IN>
RECREATION, ENTERTAINMENT, TOYS, MOVIES, PHOTOGRAPHY, SPORTS (REC)
</IN>
<LP>
   Polaroid Corp., Cambridge, Mass., said it agreed with
SMPIC, a Chinese photographic equipment maker and a unit of
the Ministry of Light Industry, to create Polaroid of
Shanghai Ltd., which will make and sell instant cameras in
China.
   The new company, which also will package film, will
initially have 130 employees.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Polaroid's venture into China is part of the photographic
equipment concern's long-term growth strategy to expand
instant photography beyond traditional geographic markets. In
the past year, Polaroid opened facilities in the Soviet
Union, India and Finland.
   Initially, Polaroid of Shanghai will assemble Polaroid
Supercolor 635CL instant cameras and package Polaroid 600
Plus instant film. Cameras and film will be marketed to
business and industrial markets, as well as to China's more
than 2,500 street photographers.
</TEXT>
